==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[organization]]
 
===Noun===
'''organisation''' (most common Commonwealth variant of '''organization''' -- note: many in the Commonwealth, especially Canadians, as well as Oxford University Press and many British publishers prefer the 'z'-spelling.)

# The [[quality]] of being [[organise]]d.
#: ''This painting shows little organisation at first glance, but little by little the structure becomes clear.''
# A [[group]] of people or other legal entities with an explicit purpose and written [[rule]]s.
#: ''In response to the crisis, the nations in the region formed an organisation.''
#: ''If you want to be part of this organisation, you have to follow its rules.''
# A group of [[people]] consciously co-operating.
#: ''Over time, the spontaneous movement had become an organisation.''

